Roethe, 223, 131, 127, 132, 134, 61, 98.|~|Two sections of a roll containing the lyrics of the German minnesanger Reinmar von Zweter, fl. ca. 1236-ca. 1260. These are the earliest witnesses to the text of Reinmar's poetry and a rare example of the form in which sung literature was transmitted while still being performed.
